<subSubSection id="D6B9258EC665FF942A9C9C1032EB7D36" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="9E1C7605C665FF942A9C9C1032EB7D36" blockId="17.[151,1437,834,2011]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis id="ACD7AA17C665FF942A9C9C1032037A3A" bold="true" box="[151,273,834,859]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males are easily distinguished from known congeners by shape of procursus (
<figureCitation id="06986A80C665FF942EA09C1036107A3A" box="[1195,1282,834,859]" captionStart="FIGURES 48–54" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1787,1809]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,202,1761]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[151,1436,193,1766]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 48–54. Mesabolivar amazonicus sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 18952). 48–49. Left male palp, prolateral and retrolateral views (arrowspoint at curved hairs on pedipalpal tarsus).50–51. Malechelicerae,lateral and frontalviews.52–53.Epigynum,ventral and lateral views. 54. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal view.Scale lines: 0.5." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202531/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 49</figureCitation>
; distinctively widened and strongly curved distal element, much smaller than in similar species, i.e. 
<taxonomicName id="59A30D86C665FF942E699C3537F17A1F" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2018" box="[1122,1251,871,894]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acrensis">
<emphasis id="ACD7AA17C665FF942E699C3537F17A1F" box="[1122,1251,871,894]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">M. acrensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="59A30D86C665FF942EF99C35367D7A1E" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2018" box="[1266,1391,870,895]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maraba">
<emphasis id="ACD7AA17C665FF942EF99C35367D7A1E" box="[1266,1391,870,895]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">M. maraba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="59A30D86C665FF942F769C35326B7AC2" authorityName=": Gonzalez-Sponga" authorityYear="1998" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudoblechroscelis">
<emphasis id="ACD7AA17C665FF942F769C35326B7AC2" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">M. pseudoblechroscelis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="59A30D86C665FF942B8C9CDE310B7AC2" authorityName="in Machado" authorityYear="2007" box="[391,537,906,931]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="huambisa">
<emphasis id="ACD7AA17C665FF942B8C9CDE310B7AC2" box="[391,537,906,931]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">M. huambisa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); also by armature of male chelicerae (
<figureCitation id="06986A80C665FF9429D99CD837447AC2" box="[978,1110,906,931]" captionStart="FIGURES 48–54" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1787,1809]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,202,1761]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[151,1436,193,1766]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 48–54. Mesabolivar amazonicus sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 18952). 48–49. Left male palp, prolateral and retrolateral views (arrowspoint at curved hairs on pedipalpal tarsus).50–51. Malechelicerae,lateral and frontalviews.52–53.Epigynum,ventral and lateral views. 54. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal view.Scale lines: 0.5." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202531/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Figs 50–51</figureCitation>
; distinctive undulating shape of apophyses in lateral view), by shape of epigynum (
<figureCitation id="06986A80C665FF9428F89CFC30677AA6" box="[755,885,942,967]" captionStart="FIGURES 48–54" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1787,1809]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,202,1761]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[151,1436,193,1766]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 48–54. Mesabolivar amazonicus sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 18952). 48–49. Left male palp, prolateral and retrolateral views (arrowspoint at curved hairs on pedipalpal tarsus).50–51. Malechelicerae,lateral and frontalviews.52–53.Epigynum,ventral and lateral views. 54. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal view.Scale lines: 0.5." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202531/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Figs 52–53</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="06986A80C665FF94298A9CFC30D97AA6" box="[897,971,942,967]" captionStart="FIGURES 69–77" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1508,1530]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,411,1486]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[151,1436,411,1486]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 69–77. Female epigyna in ventral and lateral views and cleared female genitalia, dorsal views, Mesabolivar pseudoblechroscelis group (part 2). 69–71. M. amazonicus sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 18952). 72–74. M. jamari sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 18954).75–77.M.tapajos sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 18958)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202537/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">69–70</figureCitation>
; large median depression, lateral margins diverging toward anterior, bordered posteriorly by large pocket; pair of conical lateral processes; very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="59A30D86C665FF942F769C8632167D6E" authorityName="in Machado" authorityYear="2007" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="huambisa">
<emphasis id="ACD7AA17C665FF942F769C8632167D6E" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">M. huambisa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but median pocket reaching further back in lateral view), and by female internal genitalia (
<figureCitation id="06986A80C665FF942F189CA436797D6E" box="[1299,1387,1014,1039]" captionStart="FIGURES 48–54" captionStartId="18.[151,264,1787,1809]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,202,1761]" captionTargetId="figure@18.[151,1436,193,1766]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURES 48–54. Mesabolivar amazonicus sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 18952). 48–49. Left male palp, prolateral and retrolateral views (arrowspoint at curved hairs on pedipalpal tarsus).50–51. Malechelicerae,lateral and frontalviews.52–53.Epigynum,ventral and lateral views. 54. Cleared female genitalia, dorsal view.Scale lines: 0.5." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202531/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Figs 54</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="06986A80C665FF942F739CA536857D6E" box="[1400,1431,1015,1039]" captionStart="FIGURES 69–77" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1508,1530]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,411,1486]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[151,1436,411,1486]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 69–77. Female epigyna in ventral and lateral views and cleared female genitalia, dorsal views, Mesabolivar pseudoblechroscelis group (part 2). 69–71. M. amazonicus sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 18952). 72–74. M. jamari sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 18954).75–77.M.tapajos sp. n. (ZFMK Ar 18958)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1202537/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">71</figureCitation>
; similar to 
<taxonomicName id="59A30D86C665FF942B069B4E329E7D52" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2018" box="[269,396,1050,1075]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maraba">
<emphasis id="ACD7AA17C665FF942B069B4E329E7D52" box="[269,396,1050,1075]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">M. maraba</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="59A30D86C665FF942BC39B4E314F7D52" authorityName="in Machado" authorityYear="2007" box="[456,605,1050,1075]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="huambisa">
<emphasis id="ACD7AA17C665FF942BC39B4E314F7D52" box="[456,605,1050,1075]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">M. huambisa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; pore-plates larger and slightly curved towards posterior) (female of 
<taxonomicName id="59A30D86C665FF942F769B4E326B7D36" authorityName=": Gonzalez-Sponga" authorityYear="1998" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Mesabolivar" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudoblechroscelis">
<emphasis id="ACD7AA17C665FF942F769B4E326B7D36" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">M. pseudoblechroscelis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
unknown).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
